🍃 ​̲𝑷​̲𝒍​̲𝒂​̲𝒏​̲𝒕​̲ ​̲𝑫​̲𝒊​̲𝒔​̲𝒆​̲𝒂​̲𝒔​̲𝒆​̲ ​̲𝑫​̲𝒆​̲𝒕​̲𝒆​̲𝒄​̲𝒕​̲𝒊​̲𝒐​̲𝒏​̲ ​̲𝒘​̲𝒊​̲𝒕​̲𝒉​̲ ​̲𝑮​̲𝒓​̲𝒂​̲𝒅​̲-​̲𝑪​̲𝑨​̲𝑴​̲ ​̲|​̲ ​̲𝑼​̲𝒑​̲𝒍​̲𝒐​̲𝒂​̲𝒅​̲-​̲𝒃​̲𝒂​̲𝒔​̲𝒆​̲𝒅

A deep learning–powered pipeline that allows users to **upload plant leaf images** and get real-time disease predictions with **visual explanations (Grad-CAM)**.

---
✅ 𝑭𝒆𝒂𝒕𝒖𝒓𝒆𝒔:

- 📤 Upload-based image disease detection
- 🧠 Pretrained CNN model (𝐌𝐨𝐛𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐍𝐞𝐭𝐕𝟐)
- 🔍 𝐆𝐫𝐚𝐝-𝐂𝐀𝐌 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐦𝐚𝐩 visualizations
- 🖼️ Streamlit UI for easy uploads and results

---

🔍 𝑫𝒂𝒕𝒂 & 𝑴𝒐𝒅𝒆𝒍:

- 📦 Dataset: [𝐏𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐭𝐕𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐚𝐠𝐞 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐭](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/emmarex/plantdisease)
- 🧠 Model: Trained using 𝐌𝐨𝐛𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐍𝐞𝐭𝐕𝟐
- 🔥 Explainability: 𝐆𝐫𝐚𝐝-𝐂𝐀𝐌 for heatmap visual insights

---

💻 𝑻𝒆𝒄𝒉 𝑺𝒕𝒂𝒄𝒌:

| 𝐂𝐨𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐧𝐭        | 𝐓𝐨𝐨𝐥/𝐋𝐢𝐛𝐫𝐚𝐫𝐲           |
|-------------------|-----------------------|
| DL Model          | TensorFlow / Keras    |
| Image Explainability | Grad-CAM           |
| Image UI          | Streamlit             |
| Data Source       | PlantVillage Dataset  |

---

🧪 𝑾𝒐𝒓𝒌𝒇𝒍𝒐𝒘 𝑺𝒖𝒎𝒎𝒂𝒓𝒚:

1. Upload Image via Streamlit interface  
2. Image gets preprocessed (resized, normalized)  
3. Model predicts disease label  
4. Grad-CAM generates heatmap over diseased area  
5. Final prediction + visualization shown on UI  

---

▶️ 𝑯𝒐𝒘 𝒕𝒐 𝑹𝒖𝒏 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑨𝒑𝒑:

```bash
𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦𝐥𝐢𝐭 𝐫𝐮𝐧 𝐥𝐞𝐚𝐟_𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞_𝐮𝐩𝐥𝐨𝐚𝐝.𝐩𝐲
